Warzala, Richard S. - The Wall Street Transcript













































 





































Richard S. Warzala
Richard S. Warzala, Chairman, President and CEO of Allied Motion Technologies, Inc., has a strong management and technical background in the motion control industry. Mr. Warzala joined Allied Motion Technologies Inc. as President and Chief Operating Officer in 2002, and was appointed President and Chief Executive Officer in 2009. He has served as a director of the company since 2006 and as Chairman of the board since 2014. Prior to joining Allied Motion, Mr. Warzala was President of the Motion Components Group of Danaher Corporation and held various positions at American Precision Industries Inc., including Corporate Vice President and President of its API Motion Division. His leadership experience, and company and industry knowledge, with 31 years of motion industry experience, provides valuable insight to the board of directors in formulating and executing the company’s strategy.
Related Interviews:Interview with the Chairman, President and CEO: Allied Motion Technologies, Inc. (NASDAQ:AMOT)June 17, 2016







